.TH MURAL 1 "June 2026" "mural 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mural \- per-monitor wallpaper editor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mural
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mural
is a GTK4/libadwaita application that assigns a wallpaper and fit mode to each
connected monitor, writing
.IR ~/.config/per-monitor-wallpaper/config.json .
It shows a to-scale arrangement of the connected displays; pick an image per
monitor and a fit mode (zoom, fill, fit, or center). Changes are written
immediately.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/per-monitor-wallpaper/config.json
Per-monitor wallpaper assignments written by
.B mural
and read by the per-monitor-wallpaper GNOME Shell extension.
.SH SEE ALSO
The per-monitor-wallpaper GNOME Shell extension, which reads the config that
.B mural
writes.
.SH AUTHOR
Hector Diaz
